# lirt Test Environment Variables
#
# This file is a template for .env.test which contains actual test credentials.
# Copy this file to .env.test in the same directory and fill in real values.
#
# Location: .env.test (same directory as this file)
#
# In Gas Town multi-worktree setups, each worktree can have its own .env.test file.
# For additional overrides, create .env.test.local in the same directory.

# ==============================================================================
# Linear API Test Credentials
# ==============================================================================

# Primary test API key
# Get this from: https://linear.app/settings/api
# Use a dedicated test workspace or test account for safety
LINEAR_TEST_API_KEY="lin_api_your_test_key_here"

# Optional: Override API endpoint (default: https://api.linear.app/graphql)
# LINEAR_API_ENDPOINT="https://api.linear.app/graphql"

# Optional: Test workspace ID for workspace-scoped tests
# LINEAR_TEST_WORKSPACE_ID=""

# ==============================================================================
# Test Configuration
# ==============================================================================

# Optional: Increase timeout for slow network connections (in seconds)
# LINEAR_TEST_TIMEOUT="30"

# Optional: Enable verbose test output
# LINEAR_TEST_VERBOSE="false"

# ==============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env.test:
#    cp .env.test.example .env.test
#
# 2. Edit .env.test and add your test API key:
#    vim .env.test  # or your preferred editor
#
# 3. Run tests:
#    cd refinery/rig
#    make test-api
#
# The .env.test file will be automatically loaded by tests in all worktrees.
#
# For worktree-specific credentials:
#    cd refinery/rig
#    echo 'LINEAR_TEST_API_KEY="different_key"' > .env.test.local
#
# ==============================================================================
